South Africa’s Central Bank Sells $57.9 Million of Inflation-Linked Bonds

-- B y   A n a   M o n t e i r o
-- 
2011-09-09T09:29:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-09/south-africa-s-central-bank-sells-57-9-million-of-inflation-linked-bonds.html
South Africa  sold 420 million rand
of inflation-linked bonds at an auction today where supply
exceeded demand. The central bank had offered 600 million rand
of the debt.  The bank sold 215 million rand of 2.75 percent bonds due
2022 at 2.26 percent, the central bank said on its page on
Bloomberg today. The yield compared with 2.28 percent at last
week’s sale.  It sold 10 million rand of 2.6 percent debt due 2028 at
2.27 percent, matching the yield at last week’s auction. It also
sold 195 million rand of 3.45 percent bonds due 2033 at 2.95
percent from 2.265 percent last week.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ana Monteiro at 
 amonteiro4@bloomberg.net  